PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1773515474
OL,3,CMinisters' 'inflammatory' comments led
OL,4,Cto staff abuse, say petrol retail group
OL,6,F"Our members are working hard in
OL,7,Fdifficult circumstances making sure
OL,8,Fthat motorists and businesses are
OL,9,Fgetting the fuel they need, at prices
OL,10,Fthat are very competitive, on razor
OL,11,Fthin or in some cases negative margins
OL,12,Fwhich means they are losing money. Our
OL,13,Fjob is to serve the public keeping
OL,14,Fmotorists and businesses on the road".
OL,16,F"There is clearly still a lot of work
OL,17,Fto do to help politicians and
OL,18,Fcommentators to understand how the
OL,19,Ffuel market works and our door is
OL,20,Falways open for constructive
OL,21,Fdialogue," he said.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@eO]}D@JO]
